import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['total_casualties'] = data['wounds'] + data['other'] + data['disease']
    sns.barplot(x=data.index, y=data['total_casualties'])
    plt.title('What is the total number of casualties in Crimea?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wounds')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of casualties due to wounds?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data['disease'])
    plt.title('What is the average number of casualties due to diseases?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(data['disease'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['disease'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='other', y='disease')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between casualties due to other causes and diseases?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    total_casualties = data['wounds'].sum() + data['other'].sum() + data['disease'].sum()
    percentages = [data['wounds'].sum() / total_casualties, data['other'].sum() / total_casualties, data['disease'].sum() / total_casualties]
    labels = ['Wounds', 'Other', 'Disease']
    plt.pie(percentages, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the percentage of casualties due to wounds compared to other causes and diseases?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
